node.text:
Would you drive this? 😅 Share your photos with us and we will post them in our account. Apply for a feature following the link in our bio: @tourfervor

This footage was taken in Borneo, the third-largest island in the world and the largest in Asia. Immerse in the Southeast Asia’s Malay Archipelago, is shared by the Malaysian states of Sabah and Sarawak, Indonesian Kalimantan and the tiny nation of Brunei. It’s known for its beaches and ancient, biodiverse rainforest, home to wildlife including orangutans and clouded leopards. In Sabah is 4,095m-tall Mount Kinabalu, the island’s highest peak, and, offshore, the famed dive site Sipadan Island.

📽 @khaiiidiir
📍 Kalimantan, Indonesia
🎶 JayCal PR - Me Llamaste

node.text:
Rugged (yet absolutely beautiful!) little fellow 🦜😍Apply for a feature following the link in our bio and we will publish your photos in our account: @tourfervor 

You can find the Kea parrot in the alpine regions of New Zealand’s South Island. Just park anywhere in Mount Cook or Fiordland area and watch them pick apart your car tires. Kea parrots are known to be very smart and mischievous, and incredibly rare. Have you seen a parrot like this before?

Tag someone who loves @nature! 👇

📷 @long.explorer
📍New Zealand
